The National Institute for Communicable Diseases (NICD) has reported 3 628 new COVID-19 cases in South Africa, which brings the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases to 3 631 642. This increase represents a 9.2% positivity rate. The NICD says due to the ongoing audit exercise by the National Department of Health (NDoH), there may be a backlog of COVID-19 mortality cases reported. Authorisation of new vaccines is subject to some conditions -SAHPRA  Today, the NDoH reported 213 deaths and of these, 22 occurred in the past 24â€“48 hours. This brings the total fatalities to 96 502 to date. About 22 555 062 tests have been conducted in both public and private sectors. The National Health Laboratory Service, continues to provide laboratory-based surveillance to inform the public health response towards COVID-19 in South Africa.